Shenzhen Commercial Outsourcing Investment Promotion will be held in New York\n\n

data:image/png;base64,

  	Shenzhen Business Outsourcing Investment Promotion Conference will be held in Manhattan. The conference will attract more than 150 managers from the United States staff large enterprises.  

  	&nbsp;

  	The China-U.S. Chamber Of Commerce and China Economic and Trade Office of Shenzhen City in North America jointly organize the investment conference. During the conference, Mr. Wang Xue, who is Secretary of Shenzhen Trade and Industry briefed the guests on the Shenzhen Trade Development history and current situation with particular emphasis on the advantages of outsourcing industry in Shenzhen.  

  	&nbsp;

  	Mr. Wei Lin Kuang, Chinese Deputy Consul General in New York, Mr. Hanming Liu, Chinese Mission to the UN envoy, and Edelman, U.S. Congressman, Asian Pacific American presidential advisory committee Li Xuehai and New York State Assemblyman Meng Guangrui other U.S. lawmakers attended the conference and delivered a speech  

  	&nbsp;

  	As a joint U.S. Chamber of Commerce as business community, U.S.-China Chamber of Commerce also held a staff inauguration ceremony at same day. U.S.-China Chamber of Commerce is headquartered in New York, whose purpose is to promote the development of Sino-U.S. bilateral trade, as a bridge of high-level exchanges from China and U.S. enterprises.  </embed>

  	---Translated by Luhan Tang&nbsp;
